1def rebuild(self, year, month):
2        # Every mask is 7 days longer to handle cross-year weekly periods.
3        rr = self.rrule
4        if year != self.lastyear:
5            self.yearlen = 365 + calendar.isleap(year)
6            self.nextyearlen = 365 + calendar.isleap(year + 1)
7            firstyday = datetime.date(year, 1, 1)
8            self.yearordinal = firstyday.toordinal()
9            self.yearweekday = firstyday.weekday()
10
11            wday = datetime.date(year, 1, 1).weekday()
12            if self.yearlen == 365:
13                self.mmask = M365MASK
14                self.mdaymask = MDAY365MASK
15                self.nmdaymask = NMDAY365MASK
16                self.wdaymask = WDAYMASK[wday:]
17                self.mrange = M365RANGE
18            else:
19                self.mmask = M366MASK
20                self.mdaymask = MDAY366MASK
21                self.nmdaymask = NMDAY366MASK
22                self.wdaymask = WDAYMASK[wday:]
23                self.mrange = M366RANGE
24
25            if not rr._byweekno:
26                self.wnomask = None
27            else:
28                self.wnomask = [0]*(self.yearlen+7)
29                # no1wkst = firstwkst = self.wdaymask.index(rr._wkst)
30                no1wkst = firstwkst = (7-self.yearweekday+rr._wkst) % 7
31                if no1wkst >= 4:
32                    no1wkst = 0
33                    # Number of days in the year, plus the days we got
34                    # from last year.
35                    wyearlen = self.yearlen+(self.yearweekday-rr._wkst) % 7
36                else:
37                    # Number of days in the year, minus the days we
38                    # left in last year.
39                    wyearlen = self.yearlen-no1wkst
40                div, mod = divmod(wyearlen, 7)
41                numweeks = div+mod//4
42                for n in rr._byweekno:
43                    if n < 0:
44                        n += numweeks+1
45                    if not (0 < n <= numweeks):
46                        continue
47                    if n > 1:
48                        i = no1wkst+(n-1)*7
49                        if no1wkst != firstwkst:
50                            i -= 7-firstwkst
51                    else:
52                        i = no1wkst
53                    for j in range(7):
54                        self.wnomask[i] = 1
55                        i += 1
56                        if self.wdaymask[i] == rr._wkst:
57                            break
58                if 1 in rr._byweekno:
59                    # Check week number 1 of next year as well
60                    # TODO: Check -numweeks for next year.
61                    i = no1wkst+numweeks*7
62                    if no1wkst != firstwkst:
63                        i -= 7-firstwkst
64                    if i < self.yearlen:
65                        # If week starts in next year, we
66                        # don't care about it.
67                        for j in range(7):
68                            self.wnomask[i] = 1
69                            i += 1
70                            if self.wdaymask[i] == rr._wkst:
71                                break
72                if no1wkst:
73                    # Check last week number of last year as
74                    # well. If no1wkst is 0, either the year
75                    # started on week start, or week number 1
76                    # got days from last year, so there are no
77                    # days from last year's last week number in
78                    # this year.
79                    if -1 not in rr._byweekno:
80                        lyearweekday = datetime.date(year-1, 1, 1).weekday()
81                        lno1wkst = (7-lyearweekday+rr._wkst) % 7
82                        lyearlen = 365+calendar.isleap(year-1)
83                        if lno1wkst >= 4:
84                            lno1wkst = 0
85                            lnumweeks = 52+(lyearlen +
86                                            (lyearweekday-rr._wkst) % 7) % 7//4
87                        else:
88                            lnumweeks = 52+(self.yearlen-no1wkst) % 7//4
89                    else:
90                        lnumweeks = -1
91                    if lnumweeks in rr._byweekno:
92                        for i in range(no1wkst):
93                            self.wnomask[i] = 1
94
95        if (rr._bynweekday and (month != self.lastmonth or
96                                year != self.lastyear)):
97            ranges = []
98            if rr._freq == YEARLY:
99                if rr._bymonth:
100                    for month in rr._bymonth:
101                        ranges.append(self.mrange[month-1:month+1])
102                else:
103                    ranges = [(0, self.yearlen)]
104            elif rr._freq == MONTHLY:
105                ranges = [self.mrange[month-1:month+1]]
106            if ranges:
107                # Weekly frequency won't get here, so we may not
108                # care about cross-year weekly periods.
109                self.nwdaymask = [0]*self.yearlen
110                for first, last in ranges:
111                    last -= 1
112                    for wday, n in rr._bynweekday:
113                        if n < 0:
114                            i = last+(n+1)*7
115                            i -= (self.wdaymask[i]-wday) % 7
116                        else:
117                            i = first+(n-1)*7
118                            i += (7-self.wdaymask[i]+wday) % 7
119                        if first <= i <= last:
120                            self.nwdaymask[i] = 1
121
122        if rr._byeaster:
123            self.eastermask = [0]*(self.yearlen+7)
124            eyday = easter.easter(year).toordinal()-self.yearordinal
125            for offset in rr._byeaster:
126                self.eastermask[eyday+offset] = 1
127
128        self.lastyear = year
129        self.lastmonth = month

21                self.nmdaymask = NMDAY366MASK
22                self.wdaymask = WDAYMASK[wday:]
23                self.mrange = M366RANGE
24
25            if not rr._byweekno:
26                self.wnomask = None
27            else:
28                self.wnomask = [0]*(self.yearlen+7)
29                # no1wkst = firstwkst = self.wdaymask.index(rr._wkst)
30                no1wkst = firstwkst = (7-self.yearweekday+rr._wkst) % 7
31                if no1wkst >= 4:
32                    no1wkst = 0
33                    # Number of days in the year, plus the days we got
34                    # from last year.
35                    wyearlen = self.yearlen+(self.yearweekday-rr._wkst) % 7
36                else:
37                    # Number of days in the year, minus the days we
38                    # left in last year.
39                    wyearlen = self.yearlen-no1wkst
40                div, mod = divmod(wyearlen, 7)
41                numweeks = div+mod//4
42                for n in rr._byweekno:
43                    if n < 0:
44                        n += numweeks+1
45                    if not (0 < n <= numweeks):
46                        continue
47                    if n > 1:
48                        i = no1wkst+(n-1)*7
49                        if no1wkst != firstwkst:
50                            i -= 7-firstwkst
51                    else:
52                        i = no1wkst
53                    for j in range(7):
54                        self.wnomask[i] = 1
55                        i += 1
56                        if self.wdaymask[i] == rr._wkst:
57                            break
58                if 1 in rr._byweekno:
59                    # Check week number 1 of next year as well
60                    # TODO: Check -numweeks for next year.
61                    i = no1wkst+numweeks*7
62                    if no1wkst != firstwkst:
63                        i -= 7-firstwkst
64                    if i < self.yearlen:
65                        # If week starts in next year, we
66                        # don't care about it.
67                        for j in range(7):
68                            self.wnomask[i] = 1
69                            i += 1
70                            if self.wdaymask[i] == rr._wkst:
71                                break
72                if no1wkst:
73                    # Check last week number of last year as
74                    # well. If no1wkst is 0, either the year
75                    # started on week start, or week number 1
76                    # got days from last year, so there are no
77                    # days from last year's last week number in
78                    # this year.
79                    if -1 not in rr._byweekno:
80                        lyearweekday = datetime.date(year-1, 1, 1).weekday()
81                        lno1wkst = (7-lyearweekday+rr._wkst) % 7
82                        lyearlen = 365+calendar.isleap(year-1)
83                        if lno1wkst >= 4:
84                            lno1wkst = 0
85                            lnumweeks = 52+(lyearlen +
86                                            (lyearweekday-rr._wkst) % 7) % 7//4
87                        else:
88                            lnumweeks = 52+(self.yearlen-no1wkst) % 7//4
89                    else:
90                        lnumweeks = -1
91                    if lnumweeks in rr._byweekno:
92                        for i in range(no1wkst):
93                            self.wnomask[i] = 1
94
95        if (rr._bynweekday and (month != self.lastmonth or
96                                year != self.lastyear)):
97            ranges = []
98            if rr._freq == YEARLY:
99                if rr._bymonth:
100                    for month in rr._bymonth:
101                        ranges.append(self.mrange[month-1:month+1])
102                else:
103                    ranges = [(0, self.yearlen)]
104            elif rr._freq == MONTHLY:
105                ranges = [self.mrange[month-1:month+1]]
106            if ranges:
107                # Weekly frequency won't get here, so we may not
108                # care about cross-year weekly periods.
109                self.nwdaymask = [0]*self.yearlen
110                for first, last in ranges:
111                    last -= 1
112                    for wday, n in rr._bynweekday:
113                        if n < 0:
114                            i = last+(n+1)*7
115                            i -= (self.wdaymask[i]-wday) % 7
116                        else:
117                            i = first+(n-1)*7
118                            i += (7-self.wdaymask[i]+wday) % 7
119                        if first <= i <= last:
120                            self.nwdaymask[i] = 1
121
122        if rr._byeaster:
123            self.eastermask = [0]*(self.yearlen+7)
124            eyday = easter.easter(year).toordinal()-self.yearordinal
125            for offset in rr._byeaster:
126                self.eastermask[eyday+offset] = 1
127
128        self.lastyear = year
129        self.lastmonth = month

62                    if no1wkst != firstwkst:
63                        i -= 7-firstwkst

65                        # If week starts in next year, we
66                        # don't care about it.

70                            if self.wdaymask[i] == rr._wkst:

72                if no1wkst:

75                    # started on week start, or week number 1

78                    # this year.
79                    if -1 not in rr._byweekno:

82                        lyearlen = 365+calendar.isleap(year-1)

93                            self.wnomask[i] = 1

96                                year != self.lastyear)):
97            ranges = []
98            if rr._freq == YEARLY:
99                if rr._bymonth:
100                    for month in rr._bymonth:
101                        ranges.append(self.mrange[month-1:month+1])
102                else:

104            elif rr._freq == MONTHLY:
105                ranges = [self.mrange[month-1:month+1]]
106            if ranges:
107                # Weekly frequency won't get here, so we may not
108                # care about cross-year weekly periods.
109                self.nwdaymask = [0]*self.yearlen
110                for first, last in ranges:
111                    last -= 1

113                        if n < 0:

115                            i -= (self.wdaymask[i]-wday) % 7

118                            i += (7-self.wdaymask[i]+wday) % 7

125            for offset in rr._byeaster:

3        rr = self.rrule
4        if year != self.lastyear:
5            self.yearlen = 365 + calendar.isleap(year)
6            self.nextyearlen = 365 + calendar.isleap(year + 1)
7            firstyday = datetime.date(year, 1, 1)
8            self.yearordinal = firstyday.toordinal()
9            self.yearweekday = firstyday.weekday()
10
11            wday = datetime.date(year, 1, 1).weekday()
12            if self.yearlen == 365:
13                self.mmask = M365MASK
14                self.mdaymask = MDAY365MASK
15                self.nmdaymask = NMDAY365MASK
16                self.wdaymask = WDAYMASK[wday:]
17                self.mrange = M365RANGE
18            else:
19                self.mmask = M366MASK
20                self.mdaymask = MDAY366MASK
21                self.nmdaymask = NMDAY366MASK
22                self.wdaymask = WDAYMASK[wday:]
23                self.mrange = M366RANGE
24
25            if not rr._byweekno:
26                self.wnomask = None
27            else:
28                self.wnomask = [0]*(self.yearlen+7)
29                # no1wkst = firstwkst = self.wdaymask.index(rr._wkst)
30                no1wkst = firstwkst = (7-self.yearweekday+rr._wkst) % 7
31                if no1wkst >= 4:
32                    no1wkst = 0
33                    # Number of days in the year, plus the days we got
34                    # from last year.
35                    wyearlen = self.yearlen+(self.yearweekday-rr._wkst) % 7
36                else:
37                    # Number of days in the year, minus the days we
38                    # left in last year.
39                    wyearlen = self.yearlen-no1wkst
40                div, mod = divmod(wyearlen, 7)
41                numweeks = div+mod//4
42                for n in rr._byweekno:
43                    if n < 0:
44                        n += numweeks+1
45                    if not (0 < n <= numweeks):
46                        continue
47                    if n > 1:
48                        i = no1wkst+(n-1)*7
49                        if no1wkst != firstwkst:
50                            i -= 7-firstwkst
51                    else:
52                        i = no1wkst
53                    for j in range(7):
54                        self.wnomask[i] = 1
55                        i += 1
56                        if self.wdaymask[i] == rr._wkst:
57                            break
58                if 1 in rr._byweekno:
59                    # Check week number 1 of next year as well
60                    # TODO: Check -numweeks for next year.
61                    i = no1wkst+numweeks*7
62                    if no1wkst != firstwkst:
63                        i -= 7-firstwkst
64                    if i < self.yearlen:
65                        # If week starts in next year, we
66                        # don't care about it.
67                        for j in range(7):
68                            self.wnomask[i] = 1
69                            i += 1
70                            if self.wdaymask[i] == rr._wkst:
71                                break
72                if no1wkst:
73                    # Check last week number of last year as
74                    # well. If no1wkst is 0, either the year
75                    # started on week start, or week number 1
76                    # got days from last year, so there are no
77                    # days from last year's last week number in
78                    # this year.
79                    if -1 not in rr._byweekno:
80                        lyearweekday = datetime.date(year-1, 1, 1).weekday()
81                        lno1wkst = (7-lyearweekday+rr._wkst) % 7
82                        lyearlen = 365+calendar.isleap(year-1)
83                        if lno1wkst >= 4:
84                            lno1wkst = 0
85                            lnumweeks = 52+(lyearlen +
86                                            (lyearweekday-rr._wkst) % 7) % 7//4
87                        else:
88                            lnumweeks = 52+(self.yearlen-no1wkst) % 7//4
89                    else:
90                        lnumweeks = -1
91                    if lnumweeks in rr._byweekno:
92                        for i in range(no1wkst):
93                            self.wnomask[i] = 1
94
95        if (rr._bynweekday and (month != self.lastmonth or
96                                year != self.lastyear)):
97            ranges = []
98            if rr._freq == YEARLY:
99                if rr._bymonth:
100                    for month in rr._bymonth:
101                        ranges.append(self.mrange[month-1:month+1])
102                else:
103                    ranges = [(0, self.yearlen)]
104            elif rr._freq == MONTHLY:
105                ranges = [self.mrange[month-1:month+1]]
106            if ranges:
107                # Weekly frequency won't get here, so we may not
108                # care about cross-year weekly periods.
109                self.nwdaymask = [0]*self.yearlen
110                for first, last in ranges:
111                    last -= 1
112                    for wday, n in rr._bynweekday:
113                        if n < 0:
114                            i = last+(n+1)*7
115                            i -= (self.wdaymask[i]-wday) % 7
116                        else:
117                            i = first+(n-1)*7
118                            i += (7-self.wdaymask[i]+wday) % 7
119                        if first <= i <= last:
120                            self.nwdaymask[i] = 1
121
122        if rr._byeaster:
123            self.eastermask = [0]*(self.yearlen+7)
124            eyday = easter.easter(year).toordinal()-self.yearordinal
125            for offset in rr._byeaster:
126                self.eastermask[eyday+offset] = 1
127
128        self.lastyear = year
129        self.lastmonth = month

77                    # days from last year's last week number in
78                    # this year.
79                    if -1 not in rr._byweekno:
80                        lyearweekday = datetime.date(year-1, 1, 1).weekday()
81                        lno1wkst = (7-lyearweekday+rr._wkst) % 7
82                        lyearlen = 365+calendar.isleap(year-1)
83                        if lno1wkst >= 4:
84                            lno1wkst = 0
85                            lnumweeks = 52+(lyearlen +
86                                            (lyearweekday-rr._wkst) % 7) % 7//4
87                        else:
88                            lnumweeks = 52+(self.yearlen-no1wkst) % 7//4
89                    else:
90                        lnumweeks = -1
91                    if lnumweeks in rr._byweekno:
92                        for i in range(no1wkst):
93                            self.wnomask[i] = 1
94
95        if (rr._bynweekday and (month != self.lastmonth or
96                                year != self.lastyear)):
97            ranges = []
98            if rr._freq == YEARLY:
99                if rr._bymonth:
100                    for month in rr._bymonth:
101                        ranges.append(self.mrange[month-1:month+1])
102                else:
103                    ranges = [(0, self.yearlen)]
104            elif rr._freq == MONTHLY:
105                ranges = [self.mrange[month-1:month+1]]
106            if ranges:
107                # Weekly frequency won't get here, so we may not
108                # care about cross-year weekly periods.
109                self.nwdaymask = [0]*self.yearlen
110                for first, last in ranges:
111                    last -= 1
112                    for wday, n in rr._bynweekday:
113                        if n < 0:
114                            i = last+(n+1)*7
115                            i -= (self.wdaymask[i]-wday) % 7
116                        else:
117                            i = first+(n-1)*7
118                            i += (7-self.wdaymask[i]+wday) % 7
119                        if first <= i <= last:
120                            self.nwdaymask[i] = 1
121
122        if rr._byeaster:
123            self.eastermask = [0]*(self.yearlen+7)
124            eyday = easter.easter(year).toordinal()-self.yearordinal
125            for offset in rr._byeaster:
126                self.eastermask[eyday+offset] = 1
127
128        self.lastyear = year
129        self.lastmonth = month
